column2: ingredients
Breakfast sandwich, usually with fried or scrambled egg
Pressed, toasted bagel filled with vegetables and cheese and grilled on a sandwich toaster or panini press
Canned baked beans on white or brown bread, sometimes with butter
Filling is typically meat, but can contain a wide range of foods, including sardines, tofu, pâté, or eggs. Served on an airy baguette with pickled carrots, cilantro and peppers.
Served on a bun, with chopped, sliced, or shredded meat (pulled pork, beef, or chicken typically), and sometimes topped with coleslaw
Ham and cheese, usually mantecoso, which is similar to farmer cheese
Beef (usually thin-cut steak) and cheese
Melted cheese, roast beef, tomato, and pickled cucumber in a hollowed-out French roll
Roast beef on a Kummelweck roll
Melted cheese, sliced fresh tomatoes with oregano, lettuce leaves, roast beef on Arab bread with mayonnaise.
Bacon, lettuce, and tomato. Often served on toasted sliced bread spread with mayonnaise.
Baguette bread filled with fried squid
Pre-sliced and sometimes fried bologna sausage between slices of white bread, with various condiments such as mustard and mayonnaise.

A mixture of bologna sausage and sweet gherkin pickles is processed through a meat grinder. Mayonnaise or Miracle Whip is added to the mixture. The salad mixture is left to meld flavors for several hours and then spread thickly on bread.
Usually grilled on white bread, containing a bratwurst sausage, onions, and a blend of tomato ketchup, mustard, and curry powder
The Bratwurst sandwich is a popular street food in Germany. Generally served in a roll with mustard. Some vendors offer a side dish of sauerkraut or french fries.
Typically a scrambled or fried egg, cheese, and a sausage patty or other breakfast meat, served on a biscuit or English muffin
Soft bread roll containing a ragout-based croquette, often eaten with mustard.
Consists of a shallow-fried, spicy patty, onions, and chutney or raita in a hamburger or hot dog bun.
Breaded and fried mozzarella cheese sandwich
Red caviar with butter on white bread, sometimes decorated with fresh parsley.
Sliced avocado, meat, white cheese, onions, and red sauce (salsa roja), on a fluffy sesame- seeded egg roll
Rye bread, butter and chocolate shot or chocolate sprinkles
Nutella chocolate-hazelnut spread on Italian or French bread
Thinly sliced churrasco-style steak, or lomito-style pork, with tomatoes, green beans, and green chiles, served on a round roll
Made with one or more varieties of cheese. When broiled or cooked in a pan, called Grilled Cheese.
Thinly sliced steak and melted cheese in a long roll, also known as a Philadelphia or Philly cheesesteak.
Chicken sandwich can contain chicken cooked in a variety of ways. In the United States, common forms include grilled, fried, or barbecued chicken.
Cubed cooked chicken with mayonnaise, salt and pepper.
Chickpea salad is a vegan sandwich filling with a texture similar to tuna salad. Chickpea salad consists of mashed up chickpeas, onions, and other seasonings.
Hamburger with chili con carne
Ground beef, chicken, or pork leg served on pan de agua and garnished with cabbage and Salsa rosa
Sliced white bread (or a large, flat bread roll) filled with chips, usually sprinkled with salt and vinegar or tomato ketchup.
Thinly sliced or pressed salted and dried beef. Some chipped beef is smoked to add flavor.
Filet mignon with mozzarella, tomatoes, mayonnaise, and commonly bacon, black or green olives, fried or hardboiled eggs, and ham
Made on a grill with ground beef, onions, and topped by melted cheese and served with lettuce, tomatoes, and condiments on a hero roll.
Grilled chorizo, usually served on a crusty roll with salsa-type condiments, such aspebre, salsa criolla, or chimichurri. Morcipan is a variety of this using black pudding or blood sausage.
Thinly cut steak, grilled and served on a toasted bun.
Triple-decker sandwich made with sliced turkey or chicken, bacon, tomato, and lettuce; usually contains mayonnaise
Corned beef often served with a condiment such as pickle or mustard.
Potato chips and occasionally pickles on white bread
Baked or fried ham and cheese (typically Emmental or Gruyere) brioche, sometimes coated in a mornay or bechamel sauce
Baked or fried ham and cheese (typically Emmental or Gruyere) brioche, with a fried egg on top.
Ham, roasted pork, Swiss cheese, pickles, mustard, and sometimes Genoa salami on Cuban bread, sometimes pressed and warmed in a plancha
Two thin slices of crustless, lightly buttered white bread, containing paper-thin slices of peeled cucumber
Spicy cudighi (a Michigan variety of Cotechino Italian sausage), on a long, hard roll, often topped with mozzarella and tomato sauce
Paneer (cheese), green chutney, with some butter and extra cheese

Breaded veal or chicken cutlet with provolone cheese, long hots (chili peppers) and/or sauteed greens (spinach or broccoli rabe). Sometimes served Parmigiana style with tomato sauce and mozzarella and Parmesan cheeses.
Multiple layers containing a wide variety of meats and condiments, named for Dagwood Bumstead of the comic strip Blondie

Doner kebab is meat cooked on a vertical spit, normally veal or beef but also may be a mixture of these with lamb, and sometimes chicken. This may be served wrapped in a flatbread such as lavash or pita, or as a sandwich.
Two flat fried bara (bread), containing curried chickpeas or garbanzo beans
Made of ground beef, tomato sauces, spices and many onions and peppers.
Made with a piece of dark rye bread, a layer of leverpostej, topped with a slice of salt beef and a slice of meat aspic, topped with raw onion rings and garden cress.
Peanut butter, banana, and bacon
Chopped egg mixed with mayonnaise
An open- faced sandwich consisting of an English muffin topped with meat, eggs, and hollandaise sauce
Butter and sugar on white bread.
White bread with nonpareils or sprinkles on a spread of butter. Often cut into squares or triangles.
Deep-fried balls of ground, seasoned chickpeas topped with salad vegetables, hot sauce, tahini-based sauces, and pickled vegetables, wrapped in or added to the pocket of a split-open pita bread.
Mortadella slices and cheese on buttered French bread
Crusty bread rolls filled with fish (most commonly Bismarck or soused herring) and onions
Peanut butter and marshmallow crème
Wet-cured ham, linguica, fresh sausage, steak or other roast meat, topped with melted cheese, a hot thick tomato, and beer sauce
Bun with wet-cured ham, linguica, and cheese, sauced with butter or margarine, piri-piri, and port wine, whiskey, cognac, or brandy
Thinly sliced roast beef on a baguette, served hot, usually au jus (with juice)
Fruit, such as banana, fig or pineapple served on bread, often with mayonnaise in the United States
Traditional Maltese sandwich made on a large round piece of Maltese ftira bread, topped with tomato paste, tuna, capers, and red onions.
Deli-style sandwich similar to the hoagie, often containing french fries, with other variations, prepared with masala steak, chicken, polony, Vienna sausages, calamari, fish, or chargrilled steak
Half section of Italian or French bread with garlic butter, containing ham, provel or provolone cheese, topped with paprika, then toasted
Taiwanese sandwiches consisting of a slice of stewed meat and other condiments sandwiched between flat steamed bread.
Tamale in a Mexican bolillo; also called torta de tamal
Thick unsalted flank bacon slices usually grilled on a cast iron pan and dressed with yellow mustard, slices of raw onions and tomatoes.

Pita gyro or psomaki gyro, depending on the type of bread used, includes meat roasted on a vertical spit, with tomato, potatoes, raw, often red onion and tzatziki sauce, wrapped in pita or sandwich bread.
Chocolate sprinkles or flakes usually served on buttered bread
May be accompanied by cheese. Condiments such as mustard, mayonnaise, or pickle may be present.
Common sandwich prepared with ham and sliced cheese.
Sliced Danish canned ham with sliced scrambled egg sheet in a halved sweet bun
Ground beef patty, often with lettuce, tomato, pickle, and ketchup or mustard. May include sauteed mushrooms, raw or sauteed onion, or cheese, usually on a round bun.
Hot dog wrapped in a beef patty, deep-fried, then covered with chili, a few french fries, and a fried egg
Chicken fried with fermented shrimp paste
Open-faced with turkey and bacon, topped with mornay sauce, and baked or broiled
Coarsely shredded or sliced chicken, sandwiched between two pieces of sliced bread, and completely covered with gravy. The classical version is topped with green sweet peas.
Often open-faced, sliced turkey on white bread drenched in turkey gravy, often served with mashed potatoes.
Vanilla ice cream between thin biscuits, cookies or slices of cake, normally chocolate
Thin slices of seasoned, juicy roast beef, often garnished with giardiniera or Italian sweet peppers, on a dense, long Italian-style roll
Prepared on a long bread roll or bun with meats such as salami, mortadella and capicolla along with cheese, tomato, olive oil, salt and black pepper.
Buttered bread with fruit jam, normally eaten at lunchtime or as a quick snack; may also be eaten at breakfast or for tea
French baguette with butter and ham
Meat, cheese, lettuce, and tomato, between flattened, fried green plantains (instead of bread), with garlic-flavored mayonnaise
Cheeseburger with the cheese inside the meat patty rather than on top
Breaded, deep-fried pork cutlet (tonkatsu)
A flat bread wrap with chips and sausage seasoned with salt, chilli powder and curry sauce or ketchup.
Buttered brown bread with smoked pork sausage (Kottenwurst), fresh onion rings, and spicy mustard
Meatloaf-like dish which, despite the name, contains neither liver nor cheese. It is commonly served on a Kaiser roll with mustard
Lettuce and mayonnaise
Buttered rye bread, Limburger cheese, sliced onion and mustard
Lobster meat tossed with either cold mayonnaise or hot melted butter, stuffed into a slit opening at the top of a grilled bread roll or hot dog bun
Lox on a bagel with cream cheese, thinly sliced onion, capers, and sometimes sliced tomato
Hamburger or cheeseburger on glazed doughnuts instead of a bun
White bread, butter and orange marmalade, popularised by the Paddington books
Marmite spread thinly with butter or margarine onto toast or bread
Filet americain (steak tartare) with Worcestershire sauce, pickles, onions, peppers, and martino sauce
Meatballs in marinara sauce, with melted Parmesan or provolone cheese, on a long bun or section of Italian loaf.
Roast pork, ham, mustard, Swiss cheese, and dill pickles served on sweet bread
French fries and fried meat with sauce on a demi-baguette
Open sandwich consisting of a sliced bun, topped with Mett (seasoned minced pork without bacon), frequently with a garnish of raw onion rings or diced raw onion.
Open sandwich consisting of a bolillo roll topped with refried beans, cheese and peppers, and grilled

Sliced ham and cheese (usually Emmental or Gruyere) between slices of French toast and batter-fried. In some regions it is sprinkled with powdered sugar and served with jelly or jam. In other region it is served savory with French mustard and no powdered sugar
Cured and smoked brisket with yellow mustard, usually on rye bread
Hot dog bun containing a Chicago-style corn-roll tamale, topped with chili
Meats, cheeses, and olive salad on a round bun
Pambazo bread dipped in a red guajillo pepper sauce and filled with potatoes and chorizo.

Round bread (bread bagnats) topped with green salad, tomatoes, hard-boiled eggs, tuna, anchovies, cucumbers, fava beans, artichokes, green peppers, radishes, onions, basil, and black olives. Condiments may include garlic, vinegar, olive oil, salt, and pepper. Served chilled.
Classic sandwich made famous in the kosher delicatessens of New York City
Hamburger patty, sautéed or grilled onion, and Cheddar or Swiss cheese on a bun.
Jam is often used in place of jelly. Also known as a PB&J.
Argentine sandwich with cheese, cured meat, tomato, and mayonnaise. Pebete actually refers to the bread used for the sandwich - a soft oval bun with a spongy inside, and a thin toasted crust.
Scrambled eggs and grilled bell peppers, served on French bread.
Common food preparation in the Southern United States, a spread or relish made with cheese, mayonnaise, pimentos, salt and pepper, blended to either a smooth or chunky paste.
Crusty long roll split and filled with cold cuts, roasted beef or fried seafood. The New Orleans analogue to the sub or hoagie.
Kielbasa sausage in a bun, covered with french fries, barbecue sauce (or hot sauce), and coleslaw.
A sandwich made of roast pork with italian-type spices such as rosemary, garlic, fennel and others in varying proportions.
Half-inch slice of thick sausage, usually with diced red or sweet onion, sliced pickles, ketchup, mustard, and sometimes mayonnaise, on white bread.
Popular dish in Macau, the bun is extremely crispy outside and very soft inside, containing a freshly fried pork chop.

Steak in a marinade of red wine, onions, garlic, chilies, bay leaf, parsley, oregano, ground black pepper and olive oil. The steak is grilled and placed in Portuguese rolls called carcacas. A reduced marinade based sauce is drizzled over the meats.
Selection of grilled meats topped with french fries, coleslaw, and tomato on Italian bread.
Ham and turkey topped with broiled cheese. Sometimes includes bacon and tomato.

Barbecue sandwich in which pork (usually shoulder) is smoked slowly at a low temperature until the meat becomes tender enough that it can be "pulled" or shredded with two forks. The pork is served on a bun and often topped with barbecue sauce and vinegar, or mayonnaise-based coleslaw depending on the region.
Corned beef, sauerkraut, Swiss cheese, topped with Russian or Thousand Island dressing, on rye bread, then grilled.

Sliced roast beef on bread. A variant of this sandwich is the roast beef special (deli sandwich) which is sliced roast beef, thousand island salad dressing and cole slaw served, generally, on rye bread.

Basic ingredients are eggs, chopped onions, sambal paste, salt, and pepper, cooked as an omelette with the bread added on top before it's fully cooked. Many variations include canned sardines, chicken, beef, or mutton. Garnished with mayo, chili sauce, and cheese.
Stewed pork, chopped finely, and stuffed in mo, a kind of flatbread.
Sandwich made of traditional Finnish dark rye, buttered, with lettuce, hard-boiled egg, pickles, tomato, and choice of cheese and meat (typically pork).
Bun filled with a mixture of (usually) loose meat, cabbage, and cheese. The fillings are baked inside the bread, similar to a kolache.
Pita stuffed with fried eggplant, sliced hard boiled egg, tahini sauce and Israeli salad, among other ingredients.
Hot pastrami, grilled knockwurst, melted Swiss and hot mustard on rye bread.

Made with single-, double-, or triple-layered, buttered, thin white bread with crust removed,toasted or un-toasted, containing thinly sliced meat, as well as eggs, cheese, tomatoes, green peppers, lettuce, olives, and sometimes other vegetables.
Sausage on a roll or bread, served with a variety of sauces and toppings.
Flatbread with fillings of beef, spinach, tomatoes, cucumber and tahini sauce, wrapped and grilled.

Dry hot dog bun containing guacamole, sliced cabbage, ketchup, mustard and mayonnaise. It's usually served with a sausage, but it can also be ordered with churrasco or adobado beef. Chopped onions and a variety of hot sauces are also available.
Ground meat, usually beef, cooked with seasoned tomato sauce and served on a round bun.

Multiple layers of white or light rye bread containing creamy fillings, such as egg and mayonnaise, liver pate, olives, shrimp, ham, various cold cuts, caviar, tomato, cucumber, cheese, and smoked salmon.
Open-faced, buttered dark rye bread with cold cuts, pieces of meat or fish, cheese, or spreads.
Open-faced sandwich on rugbrod, with smoked herring,chives, and a raw egg yolk.

Sizzling skewer of lamb, beef, pork, or chicken roasted, shaved off the spit, and marinade ranging from hot barbecue to sweet, on a rolled pita bread, sprinkled with your choice of lettuce, tomato, cheese, red onion, and oregano, and doused with tzatziki sauce.
Cooked spaghetti and tomato sauce on bread.
Marinated cubes of chicken, pork, lamb, veal, venison, or beef, grilled on a spit, and served in a bun.
Egg foo young patty (containing bean sprouts and minced white onions), dill pickle slices,white onion, mayonnaise, lettuce, and tomato on white bread
Grilled, over-stuffed submarine roll, containing shaved steak, and topped with salami, melted provolone, sauteed onions, and bell peppers.

Cooked steak, served on bread or a roll. Steak sandwiches may include toppings such as cheese, onions, mushrooms, bell peppers, hot peppers, tomatoes, and in some instances fried eggs, cole slaw, or french fries.

Pork roll still is the predominant term in South Jersey, but in the northern part of the state it is Taylor Ham. It is grilled pork roll served several ways. This can be served with a fried egg, or a fried egg with cheese. Commonly served on a kaiser roll.
A mixture of unseasoned ground beef and sauteed onions, sometimes topped with pickles, ketchup, and mustard, on a bun

Thinly sliced white bread with crusts removed, lightly buttered, containing a light spread of cream cheese or mayonnaise mixture, and often radishes, cucumber, asparagus, or watercress. Other fillings may be pimento cheese, ham with mustard, smoked salmon, fruit jam, curried chicken, or egg salad
Tempeh, Lettuce and Tomato. Vegan version of the BLT: smoky baked tempeh, lettuce, tomato, and avocado, served on toasted sourdough bread
Thin slice of toast between two thin slices of bread with a layer of butter, and salt and pepper to taste.
Slice of toast with ham, a maraschino cherry in the middle of a pineapple slice, and cheese, grilled from above, so the cheese starts to melt.
Tom's Tofu Toast: Toasted bread, slab of raw tofu, cucumber, tomato or roasted red pepper, spread with mayo, mustard, pesto sauce or a combination. Red onion optional. Vegan.

Mexican roll (either telera or bolillo) spread with mayo and/or refried beans and stufed with various sliced meats, cheeses, vegetables (usually tomatoes, onions and avocado) and your choice of pickled jalapeños or chipotle peppers.

Birote bread (similar to bolillo) filled with "carnitas" (deep-fried pork), shredded chicken or other meats, beans and cheese. The torta is then dipped in a very hot tomato and dried chile de arbol sauce and topped with pickled sliced onions.
Triangular white bread with the crusts removed, with fillings such as tuna and olive and prosciutto, served in Italian bars throughout the day
Slice of breaded meat, fried potatoes, a fried egg, rice, and salad (tomatoes, onions, and locotos) between two slices of bread

A combination of three meats, typically grilled, such as beef (usually churrasco steak or cube steak), roast pork (pernil), chicken, and ham. Condiments may include mustard, ketchup, and mayonnaise, often combined. Popular toppings include thin crispy fried potato sticks or shoestring potatoes, thinly sliced cabbage, lettuce, onion, tomato, pickles, and Swiss cheese. Often toasted in a sandwich press.
Tuna salad, which may include mayonnaise, sweet corn, cucumber, or celery. Other common variations include the tuna boat and tuna melt.
Potato fritter coated in chickpea flour (batata vada) in a bun

Vegemite is a dark brown Australian food paste made from used brewers yeast extract, a byproduct of beer manufacturing, various vegetables, wheat, and spice additives. It is a spread for sandwiches, toast, crumpets, and cracker biscuits, as well as a filling for pastries.
Simple and common German sandwich prepared with thin slices of lunch meat or sausage, sometimes buttered.
Hot dog bun stuffed with fried noodles, frequently topped with pickles, such as beni shoga, with mayonnaise
Halved baguette or other bread usually topped with mushrooms and cheese, ham or other meats, and vegetables
Lard on white bread, usually topped with white or red onion slices
